FBIS3-25302 "drafr031_c_94011" FBIS-AFR-94-031 Document Type:Daily Report 15 Feb 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Government Calls on UN To Stop Funding ANC, PAC MB1202073694 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 0500 GMT 12 Feb 94 MB1202073694 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The government has called on the United Nations to stop funding the ANC [African National Congress] and PAC [Pan-Africanist Congress]. In a letter to UN Secretary General Butrus-Ghali, Foreign Affairs Minister Pik Botha drew his attention to a UN resolution in terms of which funds were to be given to the two organizations until their positions in South Africa had been normalized. Mr. Botha said that in the light of political developments in the country, and the organizations' registration as political parties, the requirements of the resolution had been met.
